Stack Definition:
			Stack is a liner data structure. where insertion and deletion operations are performed from on end (side).
			stack is also know as LIFO (Last In First Out) last item served first.
		
		Used: 	Stack is used in DFS (Depth First Search) Algorithm.
			Recursion internally use stack data structure to execute the code.

monotonic stack:
			the items inside the stack in order (increasing or decreasing).
			
			Used:	when we want to find, first (greatest or smallest) value for every item.
		
